Okay, I knew that I should have researched what I was told before I
posted to the list. I hate to get the terminology wrong. They were
indeed talking about the plungers and the long & short spring being
inverted.

It turns out that I'm not able to pick it up yet, of course. The oil
pressure is still ~90psi and they fear that I might blow another filter
during the normal warm-up period. They are trying to find ways to bring
that down so I don't run into trouble.

Any thoughts? Thinner oil has been suggested, but maybe there are some
other methods? I am not sure of the performance of the oil pump and it
has been suggested that it is a "high-pressure" unit...

~Rich

